It's an initiative aimed at saving lives. COVID-19-compliant features have been fitted to more than 500 taxis at the Bara Taxi Rank in Johannesburg. This is part of the Adopt-a-Safe-Passage campaign, launched by a public-private partnership. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - COVID-19 compliant features have been fitted to more than 500 taxis at the Bara Taxi Rank in Johannesburg. This is part of the Adopt-a-Safe-Passage campaign launched by a public-private partnership. READ: Johannesburg taxis filling to capacity Public transport is one of the easiest and fastest ways for the coronavirus to spread. But for many workers living in low-income household and areas like townships, taxis are the only option when it comes to transport. Now that minibus taxis can load at 100 percent capacity for local trips, it’s become critical to ensure passengers and drivers are protected. READ: SA lockdown: Mbalula promises masks for taxi drivers, passengers More than 2,000 taxis have been fitted with these features. It's hoped with more assistance from stakeholders in the sector, 200,000 taxis will be COVID-19 compliant. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.